article.headline: S. Utah 66, UMKC 59
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Nurudeen Adepoju hit two 3-pointers in the final 2 minutes and led Southern Utah with 14 points in a 66-59 win over Missouri-Kansas City on Saturday night. Adepoju gave the Thunderbirds (15-8, 5-3 Mid-Continent) a 59-57 lead with 1:56 left with a 3-pointer, then sank another from the right corner with 20.8 seconds to play to put the Thunderbirds up 64-59. Steve Barnes clinched it for Southern Utah with two free throws with 12.2 seconds left. Dee Ayuba led UMKC (8-16, 3-5) with 16 points. Alex Pledger and Quinton Day added 10 points each for the Kangaroos, who are winless in 11 road games this season. Justin Allen scored 13 points and Tate Sorensen added 11 for Southern Utah, which led most of the way but squandered a 10-point lead late in the first half.
